A RESOLUTION
1 Congratulating Terry Holder upon his induction into the Georgia Sports Hall of Fame; and
2 for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, during his distinguished career, Terry Holder achieved an exceptional record
4 of 588-183 in baseball coaching, ranking 13th in Georgia state history for total wins and
5 becoming the first baseball coach in Georgia to reach 500 career victories; and
6 WHEREAS, he led his teams to eight state championships within a 12 year-long span,
7 earning five titles at Evans High School and three at Greenbrier High School; and
8 WHEREAS, his Evans High School teams achieved a historic 61-game winning streak
9 between 1988 and 1990 in the state's largest classification—a record that remains the longest
10 in Georgia history and ranks 14th in United States history; and
11 WHEREAS, under his leadership, the 1989 Evans High School baseball team finished with
12 an exemplary record of 29-0, earned a No. 3 national ranking by USA Today, and established
13 itself as the last undefeated baseball team in Georgia history; and
